# Glossary

## Base
An Ethereum L2 blockchain built by Coinbase.
Fast, cheap, and EVM-compatible.

## ERC-20
A standard for fungible tokens on Ethereum/Base.
BHNK is an ERC-20 token.

## ERC-721
A standard for non-fungible tokens (NFTs).
BhanksNFT follows this standard.

## Staking
Locking tokens in a smart contract to earn rewards
over time. BhanksStaking pays 1% per day.

## DAO
Decentralized Autonomous Organization. BhanksDAO
lets BHNK holders vote on protocol decisions.

## wagmi
A React library for connecting wallets and reading
from blockchains. Used throughout this project.

## viem
A TypeScript library for interacting with EVM
chains. Used under the hood with wagmi.

## OnchainKit
A React component library by Coinbase for building
apps on Base.

## Base Sepolia
The test network for Base. Free ETH available
from faucets. Use this before mainnet.

## Gas
The fee paid to process a transaction on Base.
Measured in gwei.